Speaker 2: Yeah, so I had ordered

Speaker 1: and a

Speaker 2: And are you at 3-4-1, what is that? Landrillo? Landrillo. Yep. Yep. Perfect.

Speaker 1: Okay, and I see here you got the refill. Yeah, you're a part of our VIP prescriptions.

Speaker 2: They sent you a refill looks like 60 days after the original.

Speaker 1: If you did want to keep the prescription active I can pause this service for you, Mr. Krauss.

Speaker 1: No, no, it doesn't really work for me. So I just want to cancel. Oh, you didn't get any results, huh?

Speaker 2: No.

Speaker 1: Okay. No problem. I can't cancel that for you just because you said it didn't work.

Speaker 2: I wanted to let you know if you wanted I could offer you a different type of medication if you wanted to try anything else.

Speaker 1: We do have Cialis as well. I could even send that to you like a sample, sample pack.

Speaker 2: So I wouldn't even charge you for it if you wanted to try but just wanted to offer.

Speaker 1: No, thank you.

Speaker 2: Okay. No problem, Mr. Krauss. So I'm gonna go ahead and cancel this for you.

Speaker 1: Once I cancel I won't be able to reopen the prescription.

Speaker 2: So I just wanted to make sure you're aware.

Speaker 1: We are the only FDA approved member or a vendor of this medication from Pfizer.

Speaker 2: So just wanted to make sure you didn't know that before I finalized it for you.

Speaker 1: Yep.

Speaker 2: No problem. So I did cancel that for you, Mr. Krauss. Give me just a sec.
